  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      S. aureus is the most common pathogen encountered in infection associated with cardiovascular
      surgery. StaphVAX速 is a bivalent S. aureus types 5 and 8 vaccine which contains the purified
      capsular polysaccharides (CPS) that have been implicated as a major factor in the
      invasiveness of S. aureus. Immunoprophylaxis by vaccinating against S. aureus prior to
      surgery could provide sufficient antibody concentrations during surgery and during the wound
      healing period so as to decrease the risk of S. aureus infection. This study aims to
      demonstrate the immunogenicity and safety of a single dose of StaphVAX in patients who are
      candidates for cardiovascular surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
